==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Marrow
<hw>Mar"row</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>marou</ets>,
<ets>mary</ets>, <ets>maruh</ets>, AS. <ets>mearg</ets>,
<ets>mearh</ets>; akin to OS. <ets>marg</ets>, D. <ets>merg</ets>, G.
<ets>Mark</ets>, OHG. <ets>marg</ets>, <ets>marag</ets>, Icel.
<ets>mergr</ets>, Sw. <ets>merg</ets>, Dan. <ets>marv</ets>, Skr.
<ets>majjan</ets>; cf. Skr. <ets>majj</ets> to sink, L.
<ets>mergere</ets>. ⟦root⟧274 Cf. <er>Merge</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The tissue which fills the
cavities of most bones; the medulla. In the larger cavities it is
commonly very fatty, but in the smaller cavities it is much less fatty,
and red or reddish in color.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The essence; the best part.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It takes from our achievements . . .⟦br⟧
The pith and <qex>marrow</qex> of our attribute.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <ety>[OE. <ets>maru</ets>, <ets>maro</ets>; -- perh. a
different word; cf. Gael. <ets>maraon</ets> together.]</ety> <def>One of
a pair; a match; a companion; an intimate associate.</def>
<mark>[Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Chopping and changing I can not commend,⟦br⟧
With thief or his <qex>marrow</qex>, for fear of ill end.</q>
<rj><qau>Tusser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Marrow squash</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>a name
given to several varieties of squash, esp. to the <altname>Boston
marrow</altname>, an ovoid fruit, pointed at both ends, and with reddish
yellow flesh, and to the <altname>vegetable marrow</altname>, a variety
of an ovoid form, and having a soft texture and fine grain resembling
marrow.</cd> -- <col><b>Spinal marrow</b></col>. <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<cd>See <cref>Spinal cord</cref>, under <er>Spinal</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Marrow</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Marrow
<hw>Mar"row</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Marrowed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Marrowing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To fill with, or as
with, marrow or fat; to glut.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Marrowbone</ent>⟦br⟧
